details.Clock: Running memory at 2x clock to support more concurrent ports

Additional information.text: Shallow memory implemented in RAMs instead of MLABs because MLABs cannot be configured in true dual-port mode.
RAM usage is increased from 4 RAMs to 8 RAMs because the width of individual RAM blocks in true dual-port mode is limited to 20 bits.
Requested size 128 bytes, implemented size 128 bytes, stall-free, 16 reads and 8 writes.
Banked on bits 2, 3 into 4 separate banks.
Reducing accesses to exactly one read and one write for all on-chip memory systems may increase overall system performance.
Private memory implemented in on-chip block RAM.
